From: Tim Huang <Tim.Huang@amd.com>
Date: Mon, 6 May 2024 16:21:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amdgpu: fix ucode out-of-bounds read warning
Git-commit: 8944acd0f9db33e17f387fdc75d33bb473d7936f
Patch-mainline: v6.11-rc1
References: stable-fixes CVE-2024-46723 bsc#1230702

Clear warning that read ucode[] may out-of-bounds.

Signed-off-by: Tim Huang <Tim.Huang@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_cgs.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_cgs.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_cgs.c
index b8280be6225d..c3d89088123d 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_cgs.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_cgs.c
@@ -213,6 +213,9 @@ static int amdgpu_cgs_get_firmware_info(struct cgs_device *cgs_device,
 		struct amdgpu_firmware_info *ucode;
 
 		id = fw_type_convert(cgs_device, type);
+		if (id >= AMDGPU_UCODE_ID_MAXIMUM)
+			return -EINVAL;
+
 		ucode = &adev->firmware.ucode[id];
 		if (ucode->fw == NULL)
 			return -EINVAL;
